    "id": 261,
    "text": "Playing time.\n\nThe thing that causes more parent complaints than anything else.\n\nHere's how to handle it without losing your mind:\n\n---\n\nSet expectations early.\n\nPre-season meeting:\n- How you'll select\n- What you're developing\n- That game time may vary\n\nNo surprises means fewer complaints.\n\n---\n\nDevelopment vs Winning.\n\nAt young ages (U7-U12): Rotate heavily.\nAs they get older: Performance matters more.\n\nBe clear which philosophy you're following.\n\n---\n\nTrack it objectively.\n\nSimple spreadsheet. Minutes per player per game.\n\nWhen a parent complains, you have data.\n\n\"Actually, Jamie played 47 minutes last week.\"\n\n---\n\nSubstitution patterns matter.\n\nComing on for 5 minutes at the end feels different to starting the second half.\n\nGive meaningful minutes, not token appearances.\n\n---\n\nThe honest conversation.\n\nSometimes a player IS getting less time because of performance.\n\nHave that chat privately. With specifics. With a path to improvement.\n\n---\n\nParent management templates and playing time tracking sheets are in the Football Coaching Academy.\n\nTake the emotion out of the hardest conversations.\n\nLink in bio to join."
